<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-05-28T16:51:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-05-28T16:51:00-05:00" n="328" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d328">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">788.11/5–2053: Telegram</note>
                    <head>No. 328<lb/><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in
                            Iran</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d328fn1">Drafted and signed by
                                <persName corresp="#p_RAL1">Richards</persName>.</note></head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top
                            secret<lb/>priority</hi></seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-05-28T17:51:00-04:00">May 28, 1953—5:51
                            p.m.</date></dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>3067. British Embassy Washington has received following message from
                            <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">Churchill</persName> reurtel 4474:<note n="2" xml:id="d328fn2">In telegram 4474, May 20, Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_HLW1">Henderson</persName> informed the Department that
                            he spoke with an emissary of the Shah on May 17, who said that the Shah
                            was disturbed by the British attitude toward him and wanted a clarifying
                            statement from <persName corresp="#p_HLW1">Henderson</persName> as to
                            the British attitude before <persName corresp="#p_HLW1">Henderson</persName> departed for Washington early in June.
                            (788.11/5–2053)</note>
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“You may certainly inform the State Department that while we do not
                                interfere in Persian politics we should be very sorry to see the
                                Shah lose his powers or leave his post or be driven out. Perhaps Mr.
                                    <persName corresp="#p_HLW1">Henderson</persName> will convey
                                this assurance to the Shah and say that it comes personally from
                                me.”</p></quote></p>
                    <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SWB1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>